  "title": "Visual ECoG dataset",
  "description": "This dataset comprises intracranial EEG recordings from 14 epilepsy patients implanted with clinical surface and depth electrodes, collected during visual stimulation tasks between 2017-2020. Participants viewed grayscale patterns with varied spatial and temporal properties, as well as color images from six semantic categories, while performing a fixation task. The dataset includes raw voltage data, common-average-referenced recordings, broadband responses, preprocessed epochs, and surface reconstructions with electrode localizations, enabling investigation of neural dynamics in human visual cortex.",
  "methods_description": "Intracranial EEG recordings were obtained from 14 epilepsy patients implanted with standard clinical surface (grid) and depth electrodes, with two patients additionally implanted with high-density research grids. Participants performed multiple visual tasks including population receptive field mapping with oriented bar stimuli, spatial and temporal pattern discrimination, and six-category image classification tasks. Pre-implantation T1 MRI scans were acquired for electrode localization. Data were collected across multiple sessions between 2017-2020, with common-average referencing and broadband filtering applied in derivatives.",
